Most damaging of all was the verdict of the booksellers, who dismissed the shortlist as narcoleptic. Another judge, Mr James Wood, literary critic of The Guardian, was attacked for failing to reveal that a young novelist being considered for the award, Ms Claire Messud, was in fact Mrs James Wood. Prof Bayley went on record with a rousing condemnation of contemporary fiction. Mr Kelman's book is, according to some observers, the most difficult work to have won the prize. Kelman was the least favourite of the three front runners. 